Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.15,0:02:15.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! She said that in her sleep?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.08,0:02:18.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so loud! You'll wake her up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.53,0:02:29.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As I was saying, she was sleep-mumbling\Nwhen they brought her here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.73,0:02:34.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm sorry! I'm sorry, Kudo-{\i1}kun{\i0}! I'm so sorry!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.40,0:02:36.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would she say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.77,0:02:40.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How should I know? That's just what I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.55,0:02:47.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyways, are you thirsty?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.45,0:02:50.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can get you something from the vending machine downstairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.25,0:02:52.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come with you, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.52,0:02:56.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, is Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0} all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.06,0:02:59.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! He's perfectly okay! Not a scratch on him!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.23,0:03:02.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet he's with your dad, loitering around the scene of the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.05,0:03:22.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Was it really an accident? Did they just forget to put out the candles?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.79,0:03:26.39,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}If so, then why was she asleep on the sofa when we left
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.39,0:03:29.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}but on the floor during the fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.79,0:03:32.16,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}And this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.16,0:03:36.77,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Something seems off about the furniture before and after the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.77,0:03:38.94,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Almost as if someone moved it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.94,0:03:43.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Could it be?! Did someone come back here to set the fire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.11,0:03:47.78,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}If so, then Morimoto-{\i1}san{\i0} would be most suspicious, as he had the key!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.78,0:03:49.51,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}No, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.51,0:03:54.75,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Anyone could've easily entered via a window unlocked in advance!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.75,0:03:57.69,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Think! Think!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.69,0:04:01.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}According to the witnesses, the fire started around 2:50.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.52,0:04:06.60,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}We were all in the karaoke booth at 3:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.60,0:04:12.44,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}By car, it'd take five minutes to get here. Running, it'd take fifteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.44,0:04:15.04,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}No one was gone for 30 minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.04,0:04:18.14,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}so only Noguchi-{\i1}san{\i0} could've gone there, set the fire, and returned,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.14,0:04:20.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}since he had the car key...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.38,0:04:24.21,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}The car was parked in front of the karaoke place,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.21,0:04:27.38,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}and everyone left 30 minutes before to use the station bathrooms
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.38,0:04:30.42,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}and buy cigarettes and such from the convenience store next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.42,0:04:33.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}So someone would've noticed if the car was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.72,0:04:38.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}If not the car... Chika-{\i1}san{\i0}'s motorcycle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.33,0:04:43.80,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}No, it was parked in front of the lodge when we rushed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.80,0:04:45.23,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}It's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.23,0:04:50.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}None of the people in the karaoke booth could've done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.54,0:04:54.51,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}It'd be a different story if there was a timer device of some sort,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.51,0:04:58.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}but if there had been one, the firemen would've found it long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.82,0:05:03.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Which leaves what the old guy said...\NIt was Asami-{\i1}san{\i0} who...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.85,0:05:06.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it, little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.26,0:05:08.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know you shouldn't be in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.86,0:05:10.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.49,0:05:14.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. I hear today's the birthday\Nof that girl who was asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.73,0:05:19.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The presents and the cake all burned up, but this survived the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.10,0:05:20.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.37,0:05:22.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a birthday message for her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.71,0:05:24.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Go give it to her at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.41,0:05:27.41,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Huh? They don't fit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.41,0:05:30.78,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Wait a minute! Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.78,0:05:36.19,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Come to think of it, that person did say something strange then!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.19,0:05:39.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh! Of course there was a fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.52,0:05:44.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The cake with the lit candles was sitting on a chair!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.33,0:05:48.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Mister. Was the cake really on a chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.20,0:05:51.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The chair was burnt up, and the cake turned to goop.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.73,0:05:53.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where was this chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.74,0:05:55.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's right over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.77,0:06:00.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In front of that small, charred cabinet in the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.25,0:06:11.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But doesn't it seem strange to you, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.29,0:06:12.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.36,0:06:16.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard she was in the tennis club until her 2nd year of middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.03,0:06:18.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And she was the national champion that year!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.70,0:06:21.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, that's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.00,0:06:24.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But wasn't she the soccer club manager in her 3rd year?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.47,0:06:28.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Apparently she completely changed after that summer break!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.74,0:06:30.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.64,0:06:33.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She probably wanted to focus on her studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.44,0:06:36.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- But that'd be even weirder.\N- How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.51,0:06:41.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The 2nd semester of the 3rd year is when people quit their clubs!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.28,0:06:42.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That is strange, now that you mention it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.89,0:06:46.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet she switched 'cause there were no hot guys in the tennis club.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.46,0:06:48.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right. She isn't you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.39,0:06:49.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.53,0:06:53.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, anyways, she must've had her reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.33,0:06:55.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably none of our business to pry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.87,0:06:58.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I wanna know!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.37,0:07:02.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so loud! You'll wake her up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.04,0:07:04.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Huh?\N- What? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.11,0:07:09.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}S-Sempai{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.58,0:07:12.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Customers who came in at around 3:00?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.95,0:07:15.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Do you remember who came?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.55,0:07:21.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me think. Just some youngsters doing karaoke next door, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.46,0:07:24.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They bought cigarettes, tomato juice, and other stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.26,0:07:25.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What were they like?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.76,0:07:30.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A brown-haired guy with glasses, a girl in a black dress,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.30,0:07:32.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and a guy with a buzz-cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.57,0:07:35.84,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Sawai-{\i1}san{\i0}, Hayasaka-{\i1}san{\i0}, and Noguchi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.84,0:07:40.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeesh! That buzz-cut guy puked in front of the store!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.08,0:07:42.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Cleaning it up was such a pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.35,0:07:44.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Mister. Could you tell me if...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.45,0:07:50.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko! Any luck?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.35,0:07:54.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, she wasn't in the bathroom. How about you, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.06,0:07:56.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No luck here, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.76,0:07:59.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where could Asami-{\i1}sempai{\i0} have gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.70,0:08:04.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just contact your dad for now! I'll go get a nurse!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.40,0:08:06.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.84,0:08:12.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right, little boy! How did you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.54,0:08:13.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.71,0:08:18.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I told him he had it backwards, but he didn't listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.55,0:08:23.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It had sticky stuff on it, too. What a ridiculous customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.49,0:08:26.96,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}No question about it! That person set the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.96,0:08:34.23,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}And if my theory is right,\Nthe evidence is still in their possession!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.23,0:08:37.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Asami-{\i1}san{\i0} disappeared?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.33,0:08:38.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious, Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.77,0:08:41.02,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Yeah! She was in bed just a minute ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.02,0:08:44.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She must've left while we were getting something to drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.94,0:08:46.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do, Dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.34,0:08:51.31,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Just look around outside the hospital!\NShe might still be nearby!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.31,0:08:52.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.{tune}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.82,0:08:56.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where could Asami have gone?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.82,0:08:59.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She may be planning to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.66,0:09:00.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Suicide?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.66,0:09:06.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. If it really was Asami-{\i1}san{\i0} who set the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.87,0:09:13.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Or so one might think.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.67,0:09:15.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.27,0:09:17.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the truth is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.97,0:09:21.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Asami-{\i1}san{\i0} was not the perpetrator but the victim!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.68,0:09:22.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Victim?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.71,0:09:27.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Asami-{\i1}san{\i0} was nearly burned to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.15,0:09:31.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By one of you here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.06,0:09:39.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.80,0:09:44.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the fire started when we were in the karaoke booth!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.30,0:09:47.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd take 15 minutes to run from there to here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.57,0:09:50.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Or only five minutes by car or motorcycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.51,0:09:54.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The car didn't seem to have been used,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.31,0:09:56.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the motorcycle was parked by this lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.61,0:10:02.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,None of us could have come here to set the fire then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.39,0:10:06.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Though it'd be different if there was some sort of timer device,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.09,0:10:08.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but the firefighters would've found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.59,0:10:10.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A timer device...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.46,0:10:15.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if it was something not out of the ordinary?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.23,0:10:18.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if it was something that belonged there
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.70,0:10:23.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and could be controlled from a remote location?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.77,0:10:29.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The perpetrator set the fire from kilometers away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.88,0:10:35.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By using a certain thing at a certain location near the karaoke place!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.76,0:10:40.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Little boy! Everything's ready here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.29,0:10:42.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! We'll be right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.66,0:10:44.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. What's ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.73,0:10:48.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This man asked me to have the firefighters set up the same trick
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.50,0:10:50.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that the bad guy used!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.97,0:10:52.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.90,0:10:55.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.41,0:10:58.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just such a surprisingly simple trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.74,0:11:01.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet it'll make you laugh, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.35,0:11:09.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see. It's set up like the living room before the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.52,0:11:12.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- It even has a fax machine.\N- So it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.32,0:11:14.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But how will this help?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.46,0:11:16.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.20,0:11:20.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Cake?\N- That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.53,0:11:24.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked Conan to buy some just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.47,0:11:30.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If we place it on the chair in front of the fax machine, everything's set.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.44,0:11:35.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we just wait until it starts a fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.36,0:11:45.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uhh, Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.92,0:11:50.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not suggesting we wait until a candle falls to the floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.63,0:11:52.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, if that was what happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.63,0:11:55.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that'd make it an accident caused by carelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.23,0:11:57.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I would hardly call...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.27,0:12:03.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A phone call?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.74,0:12:08.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's a fax!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.81,0:12:12.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.02,0:12:16.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.83,0:12:32.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That fax was sent by the convenience store owner at my request.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.07,0:12:35.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as the perpetrator sent one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.34,0:12:39.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- You can't be serious...\N- That's too simple!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.41,0:12:42.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the perpetrator's intent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.88,0:12:47.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The more complicated the trick,\Nthe more likely evidence will be left.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.12,0:12:49.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the idea was to simplify the trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.02,0:12:52.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,leave as little out of the ordinary as possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.29,0:12:56.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and make it look like an accidental fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.89,0:12:58.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.80,0:13:04.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You went to the convenience store to buy cigarettes at that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.97,0:13:09.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...Manabu Sawai-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.14,0:13:11.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You did it, Sawai-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.41,0:13:14.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's not true, right, President?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.28,0:13:19.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But he leapt into the flames to rescue Asami!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.82,0:13:22.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Would he really rescue someone he was trying to kill?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.65,0:13:26.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, he was the first to notice the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.32,0:13:30.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if he hadn't intended to kill her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.23,0:13:37.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if this fire was set\Nso he could rescue Asami-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.33,0:13:41.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sawai-{\i1}san{\i0} most likely did the following...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.77,0:13:45.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He dropped sedatives into her drink to make her sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.98,0:13:50.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,set up the trick just now while everyone was getting ready to leave,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.98,0:13:53.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then left the lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.82,0:13:56.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To keep Asami-{\i1}san{\i0} from burning to death, he placed her on the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.95,0:13:59.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,far away from any furniture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.69,0:14:04.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, just as he planned, while everyone was busy doing karaoke,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.36,0:14:09.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he sent a fax to the lodge and started the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.10,0:14:16.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The store owner saw him sending the fax just before the fire started.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.57,0:14:21.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The burned remnants of that fax were also found.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.18,0:14:22.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Burned remnants?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.15,0:14:25.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These! A firefighter gave them to me earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.55,0:14:29.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? The shapes don't fit, so there must've been two pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.99,0:14:35.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Only one page was sent before the fire, so it seemed strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.16,0:14:36.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.46,0:14:42.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on, now! Yes, I did send a fax at the convenience store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.00,0:14:45.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was a fax I sent to a friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.17,0:14:49.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He asked me to come up with a good title for his novel!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.61,0:14:52.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? A friend, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.68,0:14:56.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how do you explain the transmit slip?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.58,0:15:02.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You gave the transmit slip to the store owner after you sent it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.99,0:15:10.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The date, time, phone number, and your fingerprints are on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.13,0:15:14.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's strange. I'm sure I sent it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.47,0:15:16.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.87,0:15:21.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I must've dialed the wrong number!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.07,0:15:27.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? My friend's number and this lodge's number are next to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.01,0:15:31.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I'm president of Tohto University's mystery study club!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.42,0:15:34.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never use such an unreliable trick as that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.95,0:15:38.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you tested it with a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.49,0:15:43.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When you set up the living room trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.13,0:15:45.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you used the fax machine's copy feature
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.36,0:15:48.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to determine where it would catch fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.80,0:15:54.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As you know, to use the copy feature,\Nyou need to use an original.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.27,0:16:00.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you copied the birthday message Professor Takamura just sent,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.54,0:16:02.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,which was lying nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.38,0:16:08.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, you faxed that copy from the convenience store later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.49,0:16:14.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The copy that had the message and cake cream on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.66,0:16:20.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The owner complained that you stuck sticky paper in the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.30,0:16:25.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He also said he told you it was backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.37,0:16:30.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you can't blame him.\NYou sent the blank side of the copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.34,0:16:35.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because if two faxes with the same message were found at the scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.05,0:16:37.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it would raise suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.65,0:16:42.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough! I'm sick of these groundless, made-up accusations!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.32,0:16:44.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to make such claims, show some proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.59,0:16:47.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you still playing innocent?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.32,0:16:52.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You still have the fax in question.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.76,0:16:55.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,People certainly are strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.33,0:17:00.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They can't easily throw away anything that could put them in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.47,0:17:05.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They worry that someone else might pick it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.71,0:17:07.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a prime example.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.68,0:17:10.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You even brought it back from the convenience store.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.38,0:17:11.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying he...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.78,0:17:16.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He should still have it on him somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.95,0:17:23.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A fax with Professor Takamura's message and cake cream on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.69,0:17:24.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you'll excuse us...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.83,0:17:26.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.80,0:17:33.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How ridiculous! I should've just thrown this thing away!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.81,0:17:38.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Then it really was you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.74,0:17:44.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I set the fire. Using the exact method the detective explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.55,0:17:49.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But how did you know it was me? Anyone could've used that trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.92,0:17:55.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Think back to when we all rushed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.09,0:17:57.90,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Should we call her on the phone?!\NShe was asleep in the living room!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.90,0:18:01.39,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}It's no use! It's already burned up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.77,0:18:08.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Only someone who knew where the fire was could've said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.04,0:18:11.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would you do that to Asami?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.11,0:18:14.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted her to love me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.28,0:18:19.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As a brave man who risked his life\Nto rescue her from the flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.68,0:18:23.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She turned me down when I asked her out last month.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.95,0:18:27.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That had never happened to me before, so I couldn't stand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.69,0:18:32.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd planned for it to be a small fire,\Nbut it spread faster than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.36,0:18:34.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.23,0:18:38.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a small fire?! It spread faster than you thought?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.10,0:18:42.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think those serve as excuses?! You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.37,0:18:46.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why couldn't you imagine Asami-{\i1}san{\i0} possibly burning to death?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.94,0:18:51.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The car could've gotten into an accident!\NIt could've gotten a flat tire!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.28,0:18:53.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There could've been a traffic jam!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.25,0:18:58.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Asami-{\i1}san{\i0} would've lost her life\Nin any of those cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.02,0:19:00.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you wanted her to love you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.12,0:19:03.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,why didn't you consider becoming someone who could be loved?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.79,0:19:09.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you consider improving yourself instead?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.53,0:19:14.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. That was very stupid, President.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.24,0:19:15.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Asami...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.87,0:19:17.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I did something horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.11,0:19:20.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe you did this for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.11,0:19:23.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright. You can explain everything to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.41,0:19:25.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.59,0:19:33.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,President.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.16,0:19:40.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't open people's hearts with force.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.80,0:19:42.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.47,0:19:47.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you could capture any man with a single breath, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.14,0:19:53.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.38,0:19:55.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You just don't know about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.98,0:19:58.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, even I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.98,0:20:01.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...even I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.37,0:21:30.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! You confessed to Shin'ichi-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.91,0:21:33.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. I was the one who confessed my love.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.98,0:21:36.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He completely rejected me, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.11,0:21:37.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But the rumor said...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.95,0:21:41.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. I started that rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.75,0:21:46.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I really wanted him to like me.\NHe {\i1}was{\i0} my first love.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.02,0:21:50.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he didn't seem to care about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.36,0:21:54.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, there's one thing I'd like to know...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.63,0:21:58.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly about him did you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.17,0:22:02.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm. I didn't really take notice of him at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.81,0:22:06.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In his first year, he was a regular midfielder on the soccer team.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.58,0:22:09.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought he was an impressive newcomer. That's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.78,0:22:15.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But one day, I shared some lemon pie I made with the soccer club.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.39,0:22:19.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone told me it was delicious, except for him...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.92,0:22:24.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? This is kind of bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.13,0:22:26.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shin'ichi has a weird sense of taste!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.50,0:22:30.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I guess it really wasn't very good at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.57,0:22:34.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Later on, everyone said they had pretended to like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.07,0:22:39.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That hurt my feelings, so I baked a new one every day for 3 months
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.58,0:22:41.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,until he said it was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.68,0:22:45.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Before I knew it, I was manager of the soccer club
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.25,0:22:47.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and fascinated with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.48,0:22:51.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone else made it great on her first try, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.22,0:22:56.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know? I was mean and taught you a weird way of making it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.36,0:22:58.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! How come?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.83,0:23:04.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh. Shall I tell you what he said after I confessed to him, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.87,0:23:07.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Umm, say...!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.24,0:23:11.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pipe down! This is getting good! Be quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.27,0:23:14.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said this while acting embarrassed...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.41,0:23:19.18,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I'm sorry, {\i1}Sempai{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.18,0:23:23.12,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}There's someone I've been fond of since I was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.12,0:23:27.09,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}She's strong-minded and obstinate, yet easily moved to tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.09,0:23:30.04,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,500)\blur2}It's that strangeness of hers...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.29,0:23:32.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And there you have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.30,0:23:36.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on, Ran! Could that be...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.00,0:23:38.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember a girl like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.13,0:23:40.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
